				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Two emulation questions. The NTSC PPU runs at three times the speed of the CPU. Would it be right to assume that the NES runs one CPU cycle and then three PPU cycles?</div><br /><br />It's more like they run simultaneously (though they probably don't <em>really</em> run simultaneously).  After one PPU cycle, the CPU is a third of the way through its cycle, etc.  Although for emulation purposes, rounding to the CPU cycle works pretty well.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I am concerned about the PPU catching up with the CPU, especially when it comes down to palette writes.</div><br /><br />going with 3 PPU cycles for every 1 CPU cycle will work just fine for this (on NTSC).  This is why my emu and several others do, and they can handle the tight timing situations just fine.<br /><br />The PPU:CPU ratio is different on PAL though -- so if you stick to a strict 3:1 ratio it will be hard to fit in PAL support when the time comes.<br /><br />What I do is I keep my timestamps in what I call "master cycles" (some bogus term I made up):<br /><br />1 PPU cycle = 5 master cycles<br />1 NTSC CPU cycle = 15 master cycles<br />1 PAL CPU cycle = 16 master cycles<br /><br />This will keep the 3:1 ratio for NTSC, but will also give you the 3.2:1 ratio for PAL.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">What are the correct timings of the NTSC CPU and PPU. I have seen about ten different documents each providing equally differents numbers.</div>
<br />
<br />Can you be more specific as to what you're looking for?
<br />
<br />A frame consists of:
<br />
<br />1 idle scanline
<br />20 (NTSC) / 70 (PAL) scanlines of VBlank
<br />1 prerender scanline
<br />240 rendered scanlines
<br />
<br />every scanline is 341 PPU cycles -- with the exception of the prerender scanline.  On every odd frame, if the PPU is on, the pre-render scanline is 340 cycles instead of 341 (NTSC only -- PAL is always 341).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

